This paper discusses the implementation of a scalable XQuery processor for querying large repositories of XML data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.DB (Database): This sub-category covers topics related to database systems, including query processing and optimization. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): This sub-category covers topics related to distributed and parallel computing, which are relevant to the implementation of a scalable XQuery processor. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category covers topics related to data structures and algorithms, which are relevant to the optimization of XQuery processing. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): This sub-category covers topics related to programming languages, including language implementation and optimization. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): This sub-category covers topics related to software engineering, including software design and implementation.
